    "body": "Came here to second this problem. I found the same issue in McFly, which I am also reporting this bug to.\n\nFor an example of code that does NOT molest PROMPT_COMMAND when it is a Bash array, please see Direnv's example init code on my system (NixOS):\n\n```bash\n_direnv_hook() {\n  local previous_exit_status=$?;\n  trap -- '' SIGINT;\n  eval \"$(\"/nix/store/l97wg9p8zazih2r45g5fbz9b93rrj7p4-direnv-2.34.0/bin/direnv\" export bash)\";\n  trap - SIGINT;\n  return $previous_exit_status;\n};\nif [[ \";${PROMPT_COMMAND[*]:-};\" != *\";_direnv_hook;\"* ]]; then\n  if [[ \"$(declare -p PROMPT_COMMAND 2>&1)\" == \"declare -a\"* ]]; then\n    PROMPT_COMMAND=(_direnv_hook \"${PROMPT_COMMAND[@]}\")\n  else\n    PROMPT_COMMAND=\"_direnv_hook${PROMPT_COMMAND:+;$PROMPT_COMMAND}\"\n  fi\nfi\n```",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
