    "updated_at": "2025-05-17T15:29:08Z",
    "body": "I've checked the integration code of Starship, but it seems to do the right thing *under the assumption that another framework doesn't change the indices of elements in the `PROMPT_ARRAY`*. This assumption is broken by the suggested Direnv's integration code.\n\nI guess Starship tried to simplify the integration code as much as possible. While I think the Starship integration should be updated because the assumption isn't robust, I think that changing the index of elements seems a bit intrusive, too. Anyway, to me, the Direnv integration seems broken as I commented in the Mcfly issue. The Direnv integration should be fixed as well.",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "pin": null,
