    "created_at": "2025-05-24T13:35:20Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-05-24T13:35:20Z",
    "body": "When we added the array version of `PROMPT_COMMAND` to Bash 5.1, we intended that existing Bash configurations assuming the scalar `PROMPT_COMMAND` would not be broken. In that sense, the direnv integration that assumes all the other configurations use the array version of `PROMPT_COMMAND` is simply wrong. The current Bash integration of Starship (which assumes the scalar `PROMPT_COMMAND`) is nothing wrong, though we may optionally consider using the array `PROMPT_COMMAND` in Bash >= 5.1. ",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
